zip_carshare_data.name: Zipcar Station 1
zip_carshare_data.location_description: Near Community Farm and Parking Lot C
zip_carshare_data.description: Zipcar is a car-sharing service that allows students to rent vehicles on demand. Located conveniently near Community Farm, these stations provide easy access to transportation for students without personal vehicles.
benefits: Cost-effective alternative to owning a car.
Flexibility to rent cars by the hour or day.
Environmentally friendly by reducing campus traffic and parking demand.
Access to cars for off-campus errands, internships, and day trips.

departments_offices.name: Center for Leadership, Equity, and Excellence

security_gate.description: The security gate ensures the safety and security of all individuals entering the campus.

students.requirement: Husky Card or any valid government-issued ID
students.note: Students must carry their Husky Card at all times to facilitate smooth entry.

non_students.note: Visitors, including family and friends, must provide a valid government ID to gain entry.

security_gate.additional_info: The security gate staff are available 24/7 to assist with any questions or concerns. For emergencies, contact campus security immediately.

campus_sports_recreation.description: Campus Sports and Recreation provides a wide range of facilities and activities designed to promote health, fitness, and social engagement among students.

facilities.name: Fitness Center
facilities.description: Located in Haas Pavilion, the Fitness Center features state-of-the-art equipment for individual workouts and group fitness classes.

facilities.name: Tennis Courts
facilities.description: Outdoor courts available for tennis and pickleball. Equipment can be rented at the Fitness Center.
facilities.reservation_policy: Reservations can be made online or drop-ins are allowed if courts are available.

facilities.name: Aquatic Center
facilities.description: Features a 10-lane outdoor swimming pool for lap swim, water polo, and fitness classes.
facilities.hours: Varies by semester. Check the online schedule for details.
facilities.special_features: Public access available at specific times.

facilities.name: Haas Gymnasium
facilities.description: A versatile indoor facility for basketball, volleyball, badminton, and more. It also hosts intramural sports and club practices.
facilities.hours: Open for general use during non-event hours. Check the schedule for updates.

facilities.name: Pine Top Trail
facilities.description: A scenic 2.5-mile loop trail on campus for walking, jogging, and cycling. Passes through key campus landmarks, including the farm and Eucalyptus groves.
facilities.special_features: Ideal for exploring the campus’s natural beauty and staying active outdoors.

facilities.name: Soccer Field
facilities.description: Soccer field with a running track for student games, practice, and fitness activities.

activities: Intramural sports: Basketball, volleyball, badminton, and soccer
Club sports: Swimming, tennis, ultimate frisbee, and lacrosse
Fitness classes: Yoga, Pilates, spinning, and kickboxing
Outdoor excursions: Hiking, kayaking, and whale watching trips

intramural_sports.description: Recreational sports leagues organized within Northeastern University Oakland for fun and social interaction.

club_sports.description: Programs providing competitive space between other universities and teams. Includes professional or student-led teams.
goals: Provide students opportunities for intercollegiate physical activity.
Develop leadership skills through team organization.
Forge relationships and camaraderie through team activities.

excursions.description: One-time off-campus outings for exciting adventures like hiking, kayaking, and more. Registration and interest forms open at the beginning of the semester.

campus_sports_recreation.additional_info: For schedules, reservations, and upcoming events, visit the Sports and Recreation section on the campus portal or contact the office.

fw_olin_library.description: The F. W. Olin Library is a light-filled, intellectual hub on campus known for its rich collections in literature, history, women’s studies, art, and music. It provides students access to electronic databases, 240,000+ catalog volumes, rare books, and manuscripts in the Heller Rare Book Room. Students also benefit from the digital resources available through Northeastern’s Snell Library.

visiting_information.access: Students studying on the Oakland campus and in the Bay Area have full access to print resources, on-site services, and Northeastern University Library's online resources.
visiting_information.note: Check library hours before visiting and reserve study rooms for private study spaces.

resources.articles_books_search: Search for journal articles, books, and more on any topic.
resources.research_subject_guide: Use a research subject guide to get started.
resources.journal_finder: Search for a specific journal, newspaper, or other periodical by title.
resources.research_databases: View a complete list of research databases.
resources.ebook_audiobook_collection: Browse new and popular e-book and audiobook titles from the library’s OverDrive collection.

rothwell_center.description: The Rothwell Center serves as the hub for student activities, community engagement, and leadership development on the Northeastern Oakland campus.

lounges.name: Solidarity Lounge (S Lounge)
lounges.description: An empowering space for students of color and their allies, featuring a prayer/meditation room, quiet study areas, snacks, and supplies.

lounges.name: LGBTQIA2S Lounge
lounges.description: A welcoming space for LGBTQIA2S students to study, hold meetings, and gather for programs and events. Snacks, refreshments, and study materials are provided.

lounges.name: Cyclone Recreation Room
lounges.description: A recreation space with tables, a TV, bean bags, couches, board games, card games, and ping pong tables. Snacks and beverages are available nearby.
lounges.hours: Monday through Friday, 8:30 a.m.–12:00 a.m.; Saturday and Sunday, 4:00 p.m.–12:00 a.m.

lounges.name: Parenting Lounge
lounges.description: A dedicated space for student parents, featuring a play area, lactation nook, refrigerator, and study table. Access to the Mary Atkins Legacy Lounge kitchen is also provided.

lounges.name: Mary Atkins Legacy Lounge
lounges.description: A commemorative space honoring Mary Atkins, equipped with comfortable seating, snacks, coffee, tea, and communal school supplies.
lounges.hours: Monday through Friday, 8:30 a.m.–12:00 a.m.; Saturday and Sunday, 4:00 p.m.–12:00 a.m.

lounges.name: Student Leadership Lounge
lounges.description: A space for student clubs and organizations to host meetings, access supplies, and connect with peers. Includes the ASMC President’s office.

services.name: Mail and Copy Center
services.description: Mail services, printing, copying, and shipping support for students. Residential students have individual mailboxes.

services.name: Student Clubs and Organizations
services.description: A place for organizing and participating in clubs focused on academics, arts, recreation, and more. Hosts the annual Club and Community Action Fair.

leadership_development.description: Facilitates leadership opportunities for students to apply in academics, community advocacy, and professional work. Advisors support the Associated Students of Mills College (ASMC).

activities.description: Organizes a variety of social events, skill-building workshops, and other activities throughout the year.
activities.event_planning_support: Offers guidance to students planning events, even if they are not affiliated with clubs or organizations.
